Subject: Re: [VB] hoop height

> Can someone give me a measurement from the bed of a truck to the bottom of
> the hoops at the highest point?
It's about 46 1/2" to the bottom of the hoop, 48 1/8 +-" to the top of the
end cap.

> I'm looking at a truck that has cut down factory hoops. It comes with left
> over pieces from the hack, but they don't look like they would be enough to
> put the hoops back to stock height.

Cab hi hoops are generally 10-11" lower.

